The paper proposes a new method for 3D reconstruction using convolutional occupancy networks. The method involves using convolutional encoders and implicit occupancy decoders to enable structured reasoning in 3D space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves learning-based 3D reconstruction, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
